{{Infobox company | name = ENESSERE | logo = | caption = | type = | traded_as = | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 2009 | founder = | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location_city = Brendola close to Vicenza | location_country = Italy | location = | locations = | area_served = Worldwide | key_people = Alberto Tessaro, Founder; Oliver Glemser, International Business Development | industry = Renewable Energy Solutions | products = Small wind turbines | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{URL|www.enessere.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''ENESSERE''' is an Italian company, founded in 2009, with headquarters in [[Brendola]] and a manufacturer of small vertical wind turbines. Its foundation and the development of the Hercules wind turbine is a response to the [[Environmental impact of wind power]], namely to the aestethic concerns. Hercules was launched in 2015 as a piece of Design with wooden wings and applying the [[Golden Ratio]].<ref>[https://www.wired.co.uk/magazine/archive/2015/10/start/thinking-wind-turbine]/ Article about ENESSERE at wired.uk</ref><ref>http://www.designindaba.com/articles/creative-work/wind-turbine-gets-smart-tech-makeover/</ref> ENESSERE is one of the 100 energy stories that Italy provided to the [[2015 United Nations Climate Change Conference]] in Paris in December 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title= 100 ITALIAN ENERGY STORIES|url=http://www.symbola.net/html/article/100italianenergystorieseng|publisher=Symbola}}</ref>
