'''Eerikukivi''' is a [[glacial erratic]] on the island of [[Aegna]]. Its coordinates are: {{coord|59|35|10|N|24|45|14|E|}}.<ref>[http://www.unep-wcmc.org/wdpa/sitedetails.cfm?siteid=171259&level=nat World Database on Protected Areas]</ref><ref>[http://register.keskkonnainfo.ee/envreg/main?id=LO2169&mount=view Keskkonnaregistri avalik teenus] (in [[Estonian Language|Estonian]])</ref>
On 1 January 1992, the boulder was declared a Protected Natural Monument by the [[Estonian government]]. It is classed as Category III within the [[IUCN]] Management Category. The Class III designation is reserved for natural monuments that are "protected areas managed mainly for conservation of specific natural features". Or, "areas containing one, or more, specific natural or natural/cultural features which is of outstanding or unique value because of its inherent rarity, representative or aesthetic qualities or cultural significance."<ref>[http://www.unep-wcmc.org/protected_areas/categories/index.html United Nations Environment Programme Index]</ref>
