{{Infobox power station | name = Grytdalen Power Station | name_official = ''Grytdalen kraftverk'' | image = Grytdalen kraftverk.JPG | location_map = Møre og Romsdal#Norway | location_map_caption = Location in [[Møre og Romsdal]] county | coordinates = {{coord|63|6|32|N|8|33|32|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Valsøyfjord]], [[Møre og Romsdal]] | country = Norway | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = {{Start date and age|2012}} | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[Svorka Energi]] | operator = | psps_upper_res = Englivatnet | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = | psps_generators = 1 × 1.3&nbsp;MW | psps_pumpgenerators = | psps_pumps = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = [[Francis turbine]] | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_annual_generation = 5.3 | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Grytdalen Hydroelectric Power Station''' ({{lang-no|Grytdalen kraftverk}}) is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] in [[Valsøyfjord]] in the municipality of [[Halsa]] in [[Møre og Romsdal]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].<ref name="Svorka">[https://svorka.no/om-oss/datterselskap/svorka-produksjon/ Svorka Produksjon.]</ref><ref name="Spetals">[http://www.spetalsverk.no/referanse/grytdalen-kraftverk Spetals verk: Grytdalen Kraftverk.]</ref> It stands about {{convert|1.8|km|sp=us}} south of the village of [[Engan, Møre og Romsdal|Engan]]. It is a [[Run-of-the-river hydroelectricity|run-of-river]] plant that utilizes a {{convert|50|m|sp=us|adj=on}} drop from the lake ''Englivatnet'' to the intake dam of the [[Valsøyfjord Hydroelectric Power Station]].<ref name="Svorka"/> It has a [[Francis turbine]] and operates at an installed capacity of {{nowrap|1.3 [[Megawatt|MW]]}},<ref name="Spetals"/> with an average annual production of about 5.3&nbsp;GWh.<ref name="Svorka"/> The plant came into operation in March 2012 and is owned by [[Svorka Energi]].<ref name="Svorka"/><ref name="Spetals"/>
