'''Peat Wax''' is a dark waxy substance extracted from [[peat]] using organic solvents.  It is very similar to the coal derived [[Montan wax]] and therefore has similar properties and uses.  Raw peat wax is typically a mixture of three primary components, namely asphalt, resins and wax.<ref>A. J. Howard. D. Hamer,  The Extraction and Constitution of Peat Wax. A Review of Peat Wax Chemistry. The Journal of the Americal Oil Chemists' Society.  October 1960 No. 10  Vol. 37 Page 478</ref>

