The '''tomín''' (plural '''tomines''', abbreviated '''t''') is an antiquated Spanish unit of weight and currency. It was equivalent to one-eighth of a ''[[peso]]'', both in currency and weight, and derived from the Arabic term ''tomn'' ("one eighth").<ref name="Diez2007">{{cite book|author=Juan Diez|title=The Sumario Compendioso of Brother Juan Diez: The Earliest Mathematical Work of the New World|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VMPFWyZXid4C&pg=PA9|date= 2007|publisher=Cosimo, Inc.|isbn=978-1-60206-325-9|pages=9–}}</ref>
